ntly","target":"74hc595-srclr-and-oe-are-active-low-control-pins-that-must-be-tied-correctly-or-outputs-fail-silently","line":32},{"title":"esp8266-boot-pins-gpio0-gpio2-and-gpio15-must-be-in-specific-states-at-power-on","target":"esp8266-boot-pins-gpio0-gpio2-and-gpio15-must-be-in-specific-states-at-power-on","line":33},{"title":"active-level-shifters-use-one-shot-edge-accelerators-to-drive-rising-edges-breaking-the-bss138-rc-ceiling","target":"active-level-shifters-use-one-shot-edge-accelerators-to-drive-rising-edges-breaking-the-bss138-rc-ceiling","line":34},{"title":"floating-gate-pull-down-on-mosfet-is-mandatory-to-prevent-random-actuation-during-mcu-boot","target":"floating-gate-pull-down-on-mosfet-is-mandatory-to-prevent-random-actuation-during-mcu-boot","line":35},{"title":"shields","target":"shields","line":38},{"title":"eda-fundamentals","target":"eda-fundamentals","line":39}],"metadata":{"description":"The TXS0108E's OE (output enable) pin is active HIGH with no internal pull-up — leaving it unconnected lets the CMOS input drift LOW and disables all eight channels silently, which looks exactly like a wiring fault because signals reach the pins but never appear on the other side, and the standard fix is to tie OE directly to VCCA so outputs are enabled whenever the low-voltage rail is present","type":"claim","source":"docs/parts/txs0108e-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-auto-direction.md","confidence":"proven","topics":["[[shields]]","[[eda-fundamentals]]"],"related_components":["txs0108e-level-shifter"]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"key":"knowledge/txs0108e-oe-pin-is-active-high-and-floating-by-default-silently-disabling-all-outputs.md"},
